s of this really good book:<br /><br />-Very interesting main character, Theo, a reluctant hero.<br />-Very strong female character that was watching his back and she owns a restaurant/truck stop in the middle of nowhere (and can handle a gun).<br />-Lots of hicks.<br />-Takes place in Montana-Not many people there; lots of woods and unpopulated areas and you definitely feel that in the book<br />-Multiple brutal murders<br />-Bear attacks or serial killer? 300 possible bodies or more<br />-Lots of science weaved into the book, including how closed systems show patterns that the untrained observer would probably not notice<br />-You feel like they may be chasing bigfoot at some points<br /><br />Not your typical crime/thriller, but I loved it. As I said, this is something different. I will read more from this author, for sure.<br /><br />Strongly recommend!<br /><br />Mike Slavin<br />Author of award-winning thrillers <b>
  <i>Kill Crime<i></i><b></b> and Primed to Kill,Kill Crime 2</i>
